name: Sheet Pan Mahi Mahi Fajitas
author: Tammy Lynn
summary: Mahi mahi, onions, and bell peppers are cooked on a sheet pan with fajita spices. It's a tasty and easy weeknight meal that can be served in tortillas or over rice with your favorite toppings like tomatoes, sour cream, and avocado.
ingredients: 1 pinch cayenne pepper, or to taste
4 (4 ounce) mahi mahi fillets, cut into 1-inch slices
directions: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C)
Line a large baking sheet with parchment paper
Stir olive oil, lemon juice, chili powder, cumin, onion powder, garlic salt, black pepper, and cayenne together in a bowl
Spread bell peppers and onion on the prepared sheet pan
Pour 1/2 the marinade over vegetables; toss until well coated
Roast vegetables in the preheated oven for 10 minutes
While vegetables are cooking, place mahi mahi in a bowl and cover with remaining marinade; toss until well coated
Remove vegetables from the oven and set mahi mahi pieces on top
Return to the oven and cook until fish is cooked through and flakes easily with a fork, about 12 more minutes
